{
  "texts": [
    "Hoffman & Gelman 2011), with a single chain run for 10 4 steps following 10 3 warm-up steps.",
    "The posterior median of τ DRW is taken as the point estimate.",
    "We also apply JAVELIN to the first set of simulated light curves to measure τ gr.",
    "The JAVELIN light curve model includes five parameters: τ DRW, σ DRW, s gr, w gr, and τ gr.",
    "Here, s gr and w gr describe the scale and width, respectively, of the top-hat transfer function for the gr lag."
  ]
}